ciscoPsmMIB.name: ciscoPsmMIB

revisions.description: Added cpsmPortBindNextFreeTable and cpsmFabricBindNextFreeTable. Added new enumeration to the TC CpsmPortBindSwPortType.
Added a new enumeration to the TC CpsmViolationReasonCode.
Added cpsmFabricBindDenialReasonCode to cpsmFabricBindViolationNewTable and the notification ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotifyNew.
Made cpsmFabricBindDomId mandatory during creation of fabric-binding entry. Deprecated cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnTable.

Deprecated object cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnIntf. Updated description of cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnDb object to reflect the fact that fabric-binding entries cannot be cleared on an interface basis. Deprecated cpsmFabricBindViolationTable and defined new table cpsmFabricBindViolationNewTable. Deprecated ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotify and defined a new notification ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotifyNew. Added cpsmEfmdConfigTable and cpsmEfmdStatsTable.

ciscoPsmMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoPsmMIB.description: The MIB module for the management of the Port Security Manager (PSM). The PSM consists of 2 aspects: Port binding and Fabric binding. Port binding is concerned with the security of switch ports and Fabric binding with the security of the SAN fabric as a whole.

CpsmVirtNwType.name: CpsmVirtNwType
CpsmVirtNwType.description: The type of virtual network. vsan the virtual network is VSAN. vlan the virtual network is VLAN.

CpsmPortBindDevType.name: CpsmPortBindDevType
CpsmPortBindDevType.description: The mechanism used to identify the address of a device. mac the type of device address is MAC. nWwn the type of device address is Node WWN. pWwn the type of device address is Port WWN. sWwn the type of device address is Switch WWN. wildCard wild card entry (any device).

CpsmPortBindSwPortType.name: CpsmPortBindSwPortType
CpsmPortBindSwPortType.description: The mechanism to identify a switch port. fwwn the local switch port is identified by Fabric WWN(fWWN). intfIndex the local switch port is identified by ifIndex. The applicable ifType is 'fibreChannel(56)'. wildCard wild card (any switch port on local device). swwn any switch port on the switch represented by swwn.

CpsmDbActivate.name: CpsmDbActivate
CpsmDbActivate.description: Mechanism to activate/deactivate database. activate activate the database. activateWithAutoLearnOff activate the database and turn auto-learn off after activation. forceActivate activate the database and disregard errors during activation, if any. forceActivateWithAutoLearnOff activate the database and disregard errors during activation and turn auto-learn off after the activation. deactivate deactivate the database. noop no operation.

CpsmActivateResult.name: CpsmActivateResult
CpsmActivateResult.description: The result of activation/deactivation of configuration database. success the outcome of activation/deactivation was successful. actFailNullDb the activation failed because an empty configuration database was being activated. actFailConflictDb the activation failed because there were conflicts seen between the configuration database and the active database. actFailSystemErr the activation failed because of a system error. actFailAutoLearnOn the activation failed because auto learn was on. deactFailNoActive the outcome of deactivation was a failure because there was no database which was active.

CpsmAutoLearnEnable.name: CpsmAutoLearnEnable
CpsmAutoLearnEnable.description: Specifies whether to enable/disable auto learn. on enable auto-learn. off disable auto-learn.

CpsmClearStats.name: CpsmClearStats
CpsmClearStats.description: Specifies whether to clear the statistic counters. clear clear the counters. noop no operation.

CpsmClearAutoLearnDb.name: CpsmClearAutoLearnDb
CpsmClearAutoLearnDb.description: Specifies how to clear auto-learn database. clearOnVsan clear auto-learn entries on the whole VSAN/VLAN. clearOnIntf clear auto-learn entries on a specified interface on a VSAN/VLAN. noop no operation.

CpsmDiffDb.name: CpsmDiffDb
CpsmDiffDb.description: Specifes the database for difference operation. configDb configuration database to be compared with active database, with active database as the reference database. activeDb active database to be compared with configuration database, with configuration database as the reference database. noop no operation.

CpsmDiffReason.name: CpsmDiffReason
CpsmDiffReason.description: Specifies the reason for the difference. extra entry is present only in reference database. missing entry is not present in reference database. conflict entry is having a conflict between the reference database and the other database.

CpsmStatsCounter.name: CpsmStatsCounter
CpsmStatsCounter.description: Specifies a counter value which can be reset.

CpsmViolationReasonCode.name: CpsmViolationReasonCode
CpsmViolationReasonCode.description: Indicates the reason for which a switch was denied entry in to the fabric due to enforced fabric bindings. unknown(1) - Unknown reason. noSwwn(2) - The WWN of the switch that has been denied entry was not present in the list of enforced fabric bindings on the local device. domIdMismatch(3) - The WWN of the switch that has been denied entry was present in the list of enforced fabric bindings on the local device, but the domain id of the device did not match the domain id that was present in the enforced fabric binding list. efmdDbMismatch(4) - The EFMD protocol encountered a database mismatch with the switch and hence it was denied entry. noRespFromRemote(5) - There was no response from the remote device.

cpsmPortBindTable.name: cpsmPortBindTable
cpsmPortBindTable.description: This table contains the set of all valid port bindings configured on the local device. A valid port binding consists of a pWWN/nWWN bound to a port on the local device. If a device Px is bound with an interface Fx on the local device, then Px can only FLOGI thru' Fx on the local device and not thru' any other interface and Fx will permit FLOGI only from Px. Wild-cards can be specified for either Px or Fx but not for both. The set of valid port bindings configured in this table should be activated by means of the cpsmPortBindActivateTable. When the activation takes place, the valid port binding entries are enforced and FLOGI from external devices to the local device will be subject to the enforced port bindings.

cpsmPortBindEntry.name: cpsmPortBindEntry
cpsmPortBindEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindNwIndex
cpsmPortBindNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindNwType.

cpsmPortBindIndex.name: cpsmPortBindIndex
cpsmPortBindIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a valid port binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindLoginDevType.name: cpsmPortBindLoginDevType
cpsmPortBindLoginDevType.description: Specifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDev.

cpsmPortBindLoginDev.name: cpsmPortBindLoginDev
cpsmPortBindLoginDev.description: This object represents the logging-in device address. The interpretation of this object depends on the cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object is 'mac(1)', then this object contains a MAC address. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object is 'nWwn(2)', then this object contains a Node WWN. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object is 'pWwn(3)', then this object contains a Port WWN. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object is 'sWwn(4)', then this object contains a Switch WWN. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDevType object is 'wildCard(5)', then it represents a wild-card entry and this object's value will be ignored. The wild-card represents any device. This object MUST be set to a valid value before or concurrently with setting the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindRowStatus object to 'active'.

cpsmPortBindLoginPointType.name: cpsmPortBindLoginPointType
cpsmPortBindLoginPointType.description: Specifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPoint.

cpsmPortBindLoginPoint.name: cpsmPortBindLoginPoint
cpsmPortBindLoginPoint.description: This object represents the address of the port on the local device thru' which the device specified by the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginDev can FLOGI. The interpretation of this object depends on the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPointType. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPointType is 'fwwn(1)', then this object contains the fabric WWN of a port on the local device. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPointType is 'intfIndex(2)', then a port on the local device is being represented by it's interface index (ifIndex) and this object contains the ifIndex. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPointType is 'wildCard(3)', then it represents a wild-card entry and the value of this object is ignored. The wild-card represents any port on the local device. If the value of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindLoginPointType is 'swwn(4)', then this object contains the WWN of a switch in the fabric. This represents any port on that switch. This object MUST be set to a valid value before or concurrently with setting the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindRowStatus object to 'active'.

cpsmPortBindRowStatus.name: cpsmPortBindRowStatus
cpsmPortBindRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cpsmPortBindActivateTable.name: cpsmPortBindActivateTable
cpsmPortBindActivateTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries reflect the state of activation/deactivation of the valid port bindings on the corresponding VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindActivateEntry.name: cpsmPortBindActivateEntry
cpsmPortBindActivateEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. The recommended mechanism for activation is as follows: - turn off auto-learn on the required VSAN/VLAN by means of cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEnable object in the cpsmPortBindAutoLearnTable. - copy the enforced port bindings to the configuration port binding (cpsmPortBindTable) by means of the cpsmPortBindCopyTable from the cpsmPortBindEnfTable. - activate the configuration port binding using this table.

cpsmPortBindActivate.name: cpsmPortBindActivate
cpsmPortBindActivate.description: Setting this object to 'activate(1)', will result in the valid port bindings on this VSAN/VLAN being activated and the set of port bindings that have been activated will be copied to the cpsmPortBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'activateWithAutoLearnOff(2)', will result in the valid port bindings on this VSAN/VLAN being activated and copied to the cpsmPortBindEnfTable and will also result in auto learn being turned off on this VSAN/VLAN, once the activation is complete. By default, auto learn will be turned 'on' on a VSAN/VLAN after activation. Before activation is attempted, auto-learn should be off. Setting this object to 'forceActivate(3)', will result in forced activation, even if there are errors during activation and the activated port bindings will be copied to the cpsmPortBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'forceActivateWithAutoLearnOff(4)', will result in forced activation along with turning auto learn off after activation and the activated port bindings will be copied to the cpsmPortBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'deactivate(5)', will result in deactivation of currently activated valid port bindings (if any), on this VSAN/VLAN. Currently active entries (if any), which would have been present in the cpsmPortBindEnfTable, will be removed. Setting this object to 'noop(6)', results in no action. The value of this object when read is always 'noop(6)'. Activation will not be allowed on a VSAN/VLAN if auto-learn is enabled on that VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindResult.name: cpsmPortBindResult
cpsmPortBindResult.description: This object indicates the outcome of the most recent activation/deactivation.

cpsmPortBindLastActTime.name: cpsmPortBindLastActTime
cpsmPortBindLastActTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the valid port bindings on this VLAN/VSAN were last activated. If the last activation took place prior to the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object will contain a zero value.

cpsmPortBindActState.name: cpsmPortBindActState
cpsmPortBindActState.description: The state of activation on this VSAN/VLAN. If the value of this object is 'true', then an activation has been attempted as the most recent operation on this VSAN/VLAN. If the value of this object is 'false', then an activation has not been attempted as the most recent operation on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindTable.name: cpsmFabricBindTable
cpsmFabricBindTable.description: This table contains the set of all valid fabric bindings configured on the local device. A Fabric binding is specified as a switch WWN along with an insistent domain id. This set of switch WWNs represent the set of all switches that can be part of the fabric. Switches not part of this set will not be allowed to be part of the fabric. The set of valid fabric bindings configured in this table should be activated by means of the cpsmFabricBindActivateTable.

cpsmFabricBindEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindEntry
cpsmFabricBindEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindNwType.

cpsmFabricBindIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindIndex
cpsmFabricBindIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a valid fabric binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn.name: cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn
cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn.description: This object specifies the switch WWN of a switch that can be part of the fabric. This object MUST be set to a valid value before or concurrently with setting the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindRowStatus object to 'active'. This object cannot be modified while the corresponding value of cpsmFabricBindRowStatus object is 'active'.

cpsmFabricBindDomId.name: cpsmFabricBindDomId
cpsmFabricBindDomId.description: Specifies an insistent domain id. This object MUST be set to a valid value before or concurrently with setting the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindRowStatus object to 'active'. This object cannot be modified while the corresponding value of cpsmFabricBindRowStatus object is 'active'. The switch specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn will be allowed to be part of the fabric, only if it has a domain id equal to the value of this object. Attempting to pair a domain id with more than one switch or a single switch with more than one domain id, results in error.

cpsmFabricBindRowStatus.name: cpsmFabricBindRowStatus
cpsmFabricBindRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cpsmFabricBindActivateTable.name: cpsmFabricBindActivateTable
cpsmFabricBindActivateTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries reflect the state of activation/deactivation of the valid fabric bindings on the corresponding VSAN/VLAN. Entries can get into this table or be deleted from this table only by means of explicit activation/deactivation.

cpsmFabricBindActivateEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindActivateEntry
cpsmFabricBindActivateEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. The recommended mechanism for activation is as follows: - copy the enforced fabric bindings to the configuration fabric binding (cpsmFabricBindTable) by means of the cpsmFabricBindCopyTable. - activate the configuration fabric binding using this table.

cpsmFabricBindActivate.name: cpsmFabricBindActivate
cpsmFabricBindActivate.description: Setting this object to 'activate(1)', will result in the valid fabric bindings on this VSAN/VLAN being activated and the set of fabric bindings that have been activated will be copied to the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'activateWithAutoLearnOff(2)', will result in the valid fabric bindings on this VSAN/VLAN being activated and copied to the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable and will also result in auto learn being turned off on this VSAN/VLAN, once the activation is complete. By default, auto learn will be turned 'on' on a VSAN/VLAN after activation. Before activation is attempted, auto-learn should be off. Setting this object to 'forceActivate(3)', will result in forced activation, even if there are errors during activation and the activated fabric bindings will be copied to the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'forceActivateWithAutoLearnOff(4)', will result in forced activation along with turning auto learn off after activation and the activated fabric bindings will be copied to the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable. Setting this object to 'deactivate(5)', will result in deactivation of currently activated fabric bindings (if any), on this VSAN/VLAN. Currently active entries (if any), which would have been present in the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable, will be removed. Setting this object to 'noop(6), results in no action. The value of this object when read is always 'noop(6)'.

cpsmFabricBindResult.name: cpsmFabricBindResult
cpsmFabricBindResult.description: This object indicates the outcome of the most recent activation/deactivation.

cpsmFabricBindLastActTime.name: cpsmFabricBindLastActTime
cpsmFabricBindLastActTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the valid fabric bindings on this VLAN/VSAN were last activated. If the last activation took place prior to the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object will contain a zero value.

cpsmFabricBindActState.name: cpsmFabricBindActState
cpsmFabricBindActState.description: The state of activation on this VSAN/VLAN. If the value of this object is 'true', then an activation has been attempted as the most recent operation on this VSAN/VLAN. If the value of this object is 'false', then an activation has not been attempted as the most recent operation on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindCopyTable.name: cpsmPortBindCopyTable
cpsmPortBindCopyTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in copying the enforced (active) port binding database (cpsmPortBindEnfTable) to the configuration port binding database (cpsmPortBindTable) on a VSAN/VLAN. This copy operation overwrites the existing configuration port binding database.

cpsmPortBindCopyEntry.name: cpsmPortBindCopyEntry
cpsmPortBindCopyEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindCopyActToConfig.name: cpsmPortBindCopyActToConfig
cpsmPortBindCopyActToConfig.description: This object when set to 'copy(1)', results in the active (enforced) port binding database to be copied on to the configuration port binding database on this VSAN/VLAN. Note that the learned entries are also copied. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noop(2)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmPortBindLastChangeTime.name: cpsmPortBindLastChangeTime
cpsmPortBindLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last change was made to the configuration port binding database on this VSAN/VLAN. If it has not been modified since the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object will contain a zero value.

cpsmFabricBindCopyTable.name: cpsmFabricBindCopyTable
cpsmFabricBindCopyTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in copying the enforced (active) fabric binding database (cpsmFabricBindEnfTable) to the configuration fabric binding database (cpsmFabricBindTable) on a VSAN/VLAN. This copy operation overwrites the existing configuration fabric binding database.

cpsmFabricBindCopyEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindCopyEntry
cpsmFabricBindCopyEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindCopyActToConfig.name: cpsmFabricBindCopyActToConfig
cpsmFabricBindCopyActToConfig.description: This object when set to 'copy(1)', results in the enforced fabric binding database to be copied on to the configuration fabric binding database on this VSAN/VLAN. Note that the learned entries are also copied. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noop(2)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmFabricBindLastChangeTime.name: cpsmFabricBindLastChangeTime
cpsmFabricBindLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last change was made to the configuration fabric binding database on this VSAN/VLAN. If it has not been modified since the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object will contain a zero value.

cpsmPortBindEnfTable.name: cpsmPortBindEnfTable
cpsmPortBindEnfTable.description: This table contains information on all currently enforced port bindings on all VSANs/VLANs on the local device. The enforced set of port bindings is the set of valid port bindings copied from the configuration port binding database (cpsmPortBindTable) at the time they were activated. These entries cannot be modified. The learnt entries are also a part of this table. Entries can get into this table or be deleted from this table only by means of explicit activation/deactivation. Note that this table will be empty when no valid port bindings have been activated.

cpsmPortBindEnfEntry.name: cpsmPortBindEnfEntry
cpsmPortBindEnfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindEnfNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindEnfNwIndex
cpsmPortBindEnfNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindEnfNwType.

cpsmPortBindEnfIndex.name: cpsmPortBindEnfIndex
cpsmPortBindEnfIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a valid port binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDevType.name: cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDevType
cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDevType.description: This object identifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDev object.

cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDev.name: cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDev
cpsmPortBindEnfLoginDev.description: This object represents the logging in device address. This object was copied from the cpsmPortBindLoginDev object in the cpsmPortBindTable at the time when the currently active port bindings were activated.

cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPointType.name: cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPointType
cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPointType.description: Specifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPoint.

cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPoint.name: cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPoint
cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPoint.description: This object represents the address of a port on the local device. This object was copied from the cpsmPortBindLoginPoint object in the cpsmPortBindTable at the time when the currently active port bindings were activated.

cpsmPortBindEnfIsLearnt.name: cpsmPortBindEnfIsLearnt
cpsmPortBindEnfIsLearnt.description: This object indicates if this entry is a learnt entry or not. If the value of this object is 'true', then this is a learnt entry. If the value of this object is 'false', then it is not a learnt entry.

cpsmFabricBindEnfTable.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfTable
cpsmFabricBindEnfTable.description: This table contains information on all currently enforced fabric bindings on all VSANs/VLANs on the local device. The enforced set of fabric bindings is the set of fabric bindings copied from the full fabric binding database (cpsmFabricBindTable) at the time they were activated. These entries cannot be modified. The learnt entries are also part of this table. Entries can get into this table or be deleted from this table only by means of explicit activation/deactivation. Note that this table will be empty when no valid fabric bindings have been activated.

cpsmFabricBindEnfEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfEntry
cpsmFabricBindEnfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindEnfNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindEnfNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindEnfNwType.

cpsmFabricBindEnfIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfIndex
cpsmFabricBindEnfIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a valid fabric binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindEnfSwitchWwn.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfSwitchWwn
cpsmFabricBindEnfSwitchWwn.description: This object specifies the switch WWN of a switch that can be part of the fabric. This object was copied from the cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn object in the cpsmFabricBindTable at the time when the currently active fabric bindings were activated.

cpsmFabricBindEnfDomId.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfDomId
cpsmFabricBindEnfDomId.description: This object specifies the insistent domain id of the switch represented by the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindEnfSwitchWwn. This object was copied from the cpsmFabricBindDomId object in the cpsmFabricBindTable at the time when the currently active fabric bindings were activated.

cpsmFabricBindEnfIsLearnt.name: cpsmFabricBindEnfIsLearnt
cpsmFabricBindEnfIsLearnt.description: This object indicates if this entry is a learnt entry or not. If the value of this object is 'true', then this is a learnt entry. If the value of this object is 'false', then it is not a learnt entry.

cpsmPortBindAutoLearnTable.name: cpsmPortBindAutoLearnTable
cpsmPortBindAutoLearnTable.description: This table contains information on the auto learn policy for valid port bindings on all VSANs/VLANs on the local device.

cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEntry.name: cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEntry
cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndexType.name: cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndexType
cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndexType.description: This object indicates the type of virtual interface.

cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndex.name: cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndex
cpsmPortBindAutoLearnIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN for which auto learning is being enabled.

cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEnable.name: cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEnable
cpsmPortBindAutoLearnEnable.description: This object helps to 'learn' the valid port binding configuration of devices/ports logged into the local device on all its ports and populate the above enforced port binding table (cpsmPortBindEnfTable) with the same. This mechanism of 'learning' the configuration of devices/ports logged into the local device over a period of time and populating the configuration is a convenience mechanism for users. If this object is set to 'on(1)' on a particular VSAN/VLAN, all subsequent logins (FLOGIs) on that VSAN/VLAN will be populated in the enforced port binding database, provided it is not in conflict with existing enforced port bindings on that VSAN/VLAN. When this object is set to 'off(2)', the mechanism of learning is stopped. The learned entries will however be in the enforced port binding database.

cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnTable.name: cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnTable
cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnTable.description: This table contains information on the auto learn policy for valid fabric bindings on all VSANs/VLANs on the local device.

cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEntry
cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndexType.name: cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndexType
cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndexType.description: This object indicates the type of virtual interface.

cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndex
cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN for which auto learning is being enabled.

cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEnable.name: cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEnable
cpsmFabricBindAutoLearnEnable.description: This object helps to 'learn' the valid fabric binding configuration of devices logged into the fabric thru' the ports on the local device and populate the above enforced fabric binding table (cpsmFabricBindEnfTable) with the same. This mechanism of 'learning' the configuration of devices logged into the fabric over a period of time and populating the enforced fabric binding table is a convenience mechanism for users. If this object is set to 'on(1)' on a particular VSAN/VLAN, all subsequent attempts to join the fabric on some port on the local device on that VSAN/VLAN will be populated in the enforced fabric binding database, provided it is not in conflict with existing enforced fabric bindings on that VSAN/VLAN. When this object is set to 'off(2)', the mechanism of learning is stopped. The learned entries however will be in the enforced fabric binding database.

cpsmPortBindClearTable.name: cpsmPortBindClearTable
cpsmPortBindClearTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in clearing port bind statistics and/or the port bind auto-learnt entries on a VSAN/VLAN which are in cpsmPortBindStatsTable and cpsmPortBindEnfTable respectively.

cpsmPortBindClearEntry.name: cpsmPortBindClearEntry
cpsmPortBindClearEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindClearNwType.name: cpsmPortBindClearNwType
cpsmPortBindClearNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindClearNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmPortBindClearNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindClearNwIndex
cpsmPortBindClearNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmPortBindClearStats.name: cpsmPortBindClearStats
cpsmPortBindClearStats.description: This object when set to 'clear(1)', results in port bind statistic counters being cleared on this VSAN/VLAN. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noop(2)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnDb.name: cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnDb
cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnDb.description: This object when set to 'clearOnVsan(1)', results in port bind auto-learnt entries being cleared on this VSAN/VLAN. This object when set to 'clearOnIntf(2)', results in port bind auto-learnt entries being cleared on the interface specified by the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnIntf on this VSAN/VLAN. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noop'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnIntf.name: cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnIntf
cpsmPortBindClearAutoLearnIntf.description: This object specifies the interface(s) on which the port bind auto-learnt entries need to be cleared. The value of this object when read is always the zero-length string.

cpsmFabricBindClearTable.name: cpsmFabricBindClearTable
cpsmFabricBindClearTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in clearing fabric bind statistics and/or the fabric bind auto-learnt entries on a VSAN/VLAN which are in cpsmFabricBindStatsTable and cpsmFabricBindEnfTable respectively.

cpsmFabricBindClearEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindClearEntry
cpsmFabricBindClearEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindClearNwType.name: cpsmFabricBindClearNwType
cpsmFabricBindClearNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindClearNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmFabricBindClearNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindClearNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindClearNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindClearStats.name: cpsmFabricBindClearStats
cpsmFabricBindClearStats.description: This object when set to 'clear(1)', results in fabric bind statistic counters being cleared on this VSAN/VLAN. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noop(2)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnDb.name: cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnDb
cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnDb.description: This object when set to 'clearOnVsan(1)', results in fabric bind auto-learnt entries being cleared on this VSAN/VLAN. No action is taken if this object is set to 'clearOnIntf(2)' or 'noop'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnIntf.name: cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnIntf
cpsmFabricBindClearAutoLearnIntf.description: This object specifies the interface on which the fabric bind auto learnt entries need to be cleared.

cpsmPortBindDiffConfigTable.name: cpsmPortBindDiffConfigTable
cpsmPortBindDiffConfigTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in comparing the port bind active/configuration database with configuration/active database on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindDiffConfigEntry.name: cpsmPortBindDiffConfigEntry
cpsmPortBindDiffConfigEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. The user needs to configure the required type of difference on the appropriate VSAN/VLAN. The results of the difference operation will be present in the cpsmPortBindDiffTable.

cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwType.name: cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwType
cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwIndex
cpsmPortBindDiffConfigNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmPortBindDiffConfigDb.name: cpsmPortBindDiffConfigDb
cpsmPortBindDiffConfigDb.description: This object specifies the database for the comparison. This object when set to 'configDb(1)' compares the configuration database with respect to active database on this VSAN/VLAN. So, the active database will be the reference database and the results of the difference operation will be with respect to the active database. This object when set to 'activeDb(2)' compares the active database with respect to configuration database on this VSAN/VLAN. So, the configuration database will be the reference database and the results of the difference operation will be with respect to the configuration database. No action is taken when this object is set to 'noop(3)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmPortBindDiffTable.name: cpsmPortBindDiffTable
cpsmPortBindDiffTable.description: This table contains the results of the difference operation configured by means of the cpsmPortBindDiffConfigTable. This table will contain the results of the latest difference operation that has been configured. If no difference operation has been configured or if there are no differences between the databases being compared, this table will be empty.

cpsmPortBindDiffEntry.name: cpsmPortBindDiffEntry
cpsmPortBindDiffEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindDiffNwType.name: cpsmPortBindDiffNwType
cpsmPortBindDiffNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindDiffNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmPortBindDiffNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindDiffNwIndex
cpsmPortBindDiffNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmPortBindDiffIndex.name: cpsmPortBindDiffIndex
cpsmPortBindDiffIndex.description: The index of this entry. This represents the index of a port binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindDiffReason.name: cpsmPortBindDiffReason
cpsmPortBindDiffReason.description: This object indicates the reason for the difference between the databases being compared, for this entry.

cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDevType.name: cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDevType
cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDevType.description: This object identifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDev object.

cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDev.name: cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDev
cpsmPortBindDiffLoginDev.description: This object represents the logging in device address. This object was copied either from the cpsmPortBindLoginDev object in the cpsmPortBindTable or from the cpsmPortBindEnfLoginIdev object in the cpsmPortBindEnfTable at the time when the difference operation was done.

cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPointType.name: cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPointType
cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPointType.description: Specifies the format of the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPoint.

cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPoint.name: cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPoint
cpsmPortBindDiffLoginPoint.description: This object represents the address of a port on the local device. This object was copied either from the cpsmPortBindLoginPoint object in the cpsmPortBindTable or from the cpsmPortBindEnfLoginPoint object in the cpsmPortBindEnfTable at the time when the difference operation was done.

cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigTable.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigTable
cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigTable.description: This table contains atmost one entry per VSAN/VLAN that is configured. These entries help in comparing the fabric bind active/configuration database with configuration/active database on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigEntry
cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. The user needs to configure the required type of difference on the appropriate VSAN/VLAN. The results of the difference operation will be present in the cpsmFabricBindDiffTable.

cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwType.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwType
cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigDb.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigDb
cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigDb.description: This object specifies the database for the comparison. This object when set to 'configDb(1)' compares the fabric bind configuration database with respect to active database on this VSAN/VLAN. So, the active database will be the reference database and the results of the difference operation will be with respect to the active database. This object when set to 'activeDb(2)' compares the fabric bind active database with respect to configuration database on this VSAN/VLAN. So, the configuration database will be the reference database and the results of the difference operation will be with respect to the configuration database. No action is taken when this object is set to 'noop(3)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop'.

cpsmFabricBindDiffTable.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffTable
cpsmFabricBindDiffTable.description: This table contains the results of the difference operation configured by means of the cpsmFabricBindDiffConfigTable. This table will contain the results of the latest difference operation that has been configured. If no difference operation has been configured or if there are no differences between the databases being compared, this table will be empty.

cpsmFabricBindDiffEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffEntry
cpsmFabricBindDiffEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindDiffNwType.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffNwType
cpsmFabricBindDiffNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindDiffNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmFabricBindDiffNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindDiffNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindDiffIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffIndex
cpsmFabricBindDiffIndex.description: The index of this entry. This represents the index of a fabric binding on a VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindDiffReason.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffReason
cpsmFabricBindDiffReason.description: This object indicates the reason for the difference between the databases being compared, for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindDiffSwitchWwn.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffSwitchWwn
cpsmFabricBindDiffSwitchWwn.description: This object specifies the WWN of a switch that can be part of the fabric. This object was copied either from the cpsmFabricBindSwitchWwn object in the cpsmFabricBindTable or from the cpsmFabricBindEnfSwitchWwn object in the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable at the time when the difference operation was done.

cpsmFabricBindDiffDomId.name: cpsmFabricBindDiffDomId
cpsmFabricBindDiffDomId.description: This object specifies the insistent domain id of the switch represented by the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindDiffSwitchWwn. This object was copied either from the cpsmFabricBindDomId object in the cpsmFabricBindTable or from the cpsmFabricBindEnfDomId object in the cpsmFabricBindEnfTable when the difference operation was done.

cpsmPortBindStatsTable.name: cpsmPortBindStatsTable
cpsmPortBindStatsTable.description: This table contains statistic counters maintained on a per VSAN/VLAN basis on the local device for enforced port bindings.

cpsmPortBindStatsEntry.name: cpsmPortBindStatsEntry
cpsmPortBindStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindVsanVlanType.name: cpsmPortBindVsanVlanType
cpsmPortBindVsanVlanType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindVsanVlanIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmPortBindVsanVlanIndex.name: cpsmPortBindVsanVlanIndex
cpsmPortBindVsanVlanIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmPortBindAllowedLogins.name: cpsmPortBindAllowedLogins
cpsmPortBindAllowedLogins.description: The number of FLOGI requests that have been allowed on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindDeniedLogins.name: cpsmPortBindDeniedLogins
cpsmPortBindDeniedLogins.description: The number of FLOGI requests that have been denied on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindStatsTable.name: cpsmFabricBindStatsTable
cpsmFabricBindStatsTable.description: This table contains statistic counters maintained on a per VSAN/VLAN basis on the local device for enforced fabric bindings.

cpsmFabricBindStatsEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindStatsEntry
cpsmFabricBindStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanType.name: cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanType
cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanIndex
cpsmFabricBindVsanVlanIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindAllowedReqs.name: cpsmFabricBindAllowedReqs
cpsmFabricBindAllowedReqs.description: The number of requests from switches to become part of the fabric that have been allowed on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindDeniedReqs.name: cpsmFabricBindDeniedReqs
cpsmFabricBindDeniedReqs.description: The number of requests from switches to become part of the fabric that have been denied on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmPortBindViolationTable.name: cpsmPortBindViolationTable
cpsmPortBindViolationTable.description: This table contains information on atmost the last 100 login violations that have been detected on the local device for enforced port bindings. When the number of such entries exceeds 100, then there is a wrap-around that takes place and the entries get over-written starting from the first entry.

cpsmPortBindViolationEntry.name: cpsmPortBindViolationEntry
cpsmPortBindViolationEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindViolationNwType.name: cpsmPortBindViolationNwType
cpsmPortBindViolationNwType.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindViolationNwIndex object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmPortBindViolationNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindViolationNwIndex
cpsmPortBindViolationNwIndex.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmPortBindLoginPwwn.name: cpsmPortBindLoginPwwn
cpsmPortBindLoginPwwn.description: The pWWN of the device that was denied FLOGI on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmPortBindLoginNwwn.name: cpsmPortBindLoginNwwn
cpsmPortBindLoginNwwn.description: The nWWN of the device that was denied FLOGI on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmPortBindLoginSwwn.name: cpsmPortBindLoginSwwn
cpsmPortBindLoginSwwn.description: The sWWN of the device (if the device happens to be a switch), that was denied entry on one of the local device's ports. If the device is a switch, then the corresponding instances of cpsmPortBindLoginNwwn and cpsmPortBindLoginPwwn will contain zero-length strings.

cpsmPortBindLoginPort.name: cpsmPortBindLoginPort
cpsmPortBindLoginPort.description: The fWWN of the port on the local device where the login was denied.

cpsmPortBindLoginTime.name: cpsmPortBindLoginTime
cpsmPortBindLoginTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the login denial took place.

cpsmPortBindLoginCount.name: cpsmPortBindLoginCount
cpsmPortBindLoginCount.description: The number of times this particular pWWN/nWWN or sWWN has been denied login on this particular local interface.

cpsmPortBindLoginIntf.name: cpsmPortBindLoginIntf
cpsmPortBindLoginIntf.description: The ifIndex of the port on the local device where the login was denied.

cpsmFabricBindViolationTable.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationTable
cpsmFabricBindViolationTable.description: This table contains information on atmost the last 100 violations that have been detected on the local device for enforced fabric bindings. When the number of such entries exceeds 100, then there is a wrap-around that takes place and the entries get over-written starting from the first entry.

cpsmFabricBindViolationEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationEntry
cpsmFabricBindViolationEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindSwwn.name: cpsmFabricBindSwwn
cpsmFabricBindSwwn.description: The sWWN (switch WWN) of the device that was denied entry into the fabric on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmFabricBindLocalPort.name: cpsmFabricBindLocalPort
cpsmFabricBindLocalPort.description: The fWWN of the port on the local device where the denial took place.

cpsmFabricBindDenialTime.name: cpsmFabricBindDenialTime
cpsmFabricBindDenialTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the denial took place.

cpsmFabricBindLocalIntf.name: cpsmFabricBindLocalIntf
cpsmFabricBindLocalIntf.description: The ifIndex of the port on the local device where the denial took place.

cpsmFabricBindViolationNewTable.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationNewTable
cpsmFabricBindViolationNewTable.description: This table contains information on atmost the last 100 violations that have been detected on the local device for enforced fabric bindings. When the number of such entries exceeds 100, then there is a wrap-around that takes place and the entries get over-written starting from the first entry.

cpsmFabricBindViolationNewEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationNewEntry
cpsmFabricBindViolationNewEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindViolationNwTypeR1.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationNwTypeR1
cpsmFabricBindViolationNwTypeR1.description: This object indicates whether the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindViolationNwIndexR1 object contains a VSAN id or VLAN id.

cpsmFabricBindViolationNwIndexR1.name: cpsmFabricBindViolationNwIndexR1
cpsmFabricBindViolationNwIndexR1.description: The VSAN/VLAN id for this entry.

cpsmFabricBindSwwnR1.name: cpsmFabricBindSwwnR1
cpsmFabricBindSwwnR1.description: The sWWN (switch WWN) of the device that was denied entry into the fabric on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmFabricBindDenialTimeR1.name: cpsmFabricBindDenialTimeR1
cpsmFabricBindDenialTimeR1.description: The sysUpTime at which the denial took place.

cpsmFabricBindDenialCountR1.name: cpsmFabricBindDenialCountR1
cpsmFabricBindDenialCountR1.description: The number of times this switch has been denied entry into the fabric on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmFabricBindDenialDomId.name: cpsmFabricBindDenialDomId
cpsmFabricBindDenialDomId.description: The domain id of the device that was denied entry into the fabric on one of the local device's ports. A value of zero indicates that the switch WWN of the device was not present in the enforced fabric bindings.

cpsmFabricBindDenialReasonCode.name: cpsmFabricBindDenialReasonCode
cpsmFabricBindDenialReasonCode.description: The reason for which the device was denied entry into the fabric on one of the local device's ports.

cpsmEfmdStatsTable.name: cpsmEfmdStatsTable
cpsmEfmdStatsTable.description: This table contains the EFMD protocol statistics on a per VSAN basis.

cpsmEfmdStatsEntry.name: cpsmEfmdStatsEntry
cpsmEfmdStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmEfmdTxMergeReqs.name: cpsmEfmdTxMergeReqs
cpsmEfmdTxMergeReqs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Requests transmitted on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdRxMergeReqs.name: cpsmEfmdRxMergeReqs
cpsmEfmdRxMergeReqs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Requests received on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdTxMergeAccs.name: cpsmEfmdTxMergeAccs
cpsmEfmdTxMergeAccs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Accepts transmitted on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdRxMergeAccs.name: cpsmEfmdRxMergeAccs
cpsmEfmdRxMergeAccs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Accepts received on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdTxMergeRejs.name: cpsmEfmdTxMergeRejs
cpsmEfmdTxMergeRejs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Rejects transmitted on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdRxMergeRejs.name: cpsmEfmdRxMergeRejs
cpsmEfmdRxMergeRejs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Rejects received on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdTxMergeBusys.name: cpsmEfmdTxMergeBusys
cpsmEfmdTxMergeBusys.description: The number of EFMD Merge Busys transmitted on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdRxMergeBusys.name: cpsmEfmdRxMergeBusys
cpsmEfmdRxMergeBusys.description: The number of EFMD Merge Busys received on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdTxMergeErrs.name: cpsmEfmdTxMergeErrs
cpsmEfmdTxMergeErrs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Errors transmitted on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmEfmdRxMergeErrs.name: cpsmEfmdRxMergeErrs
cpsmEfmdRxMergeErrs.description: The number of EFMD Merge Errors received on this VSAN by the local device.

cpsmNotifyEnable.name: cpsmNotifyEnable
cpsmNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if the Security Policy Manager notifications should be generated or not. If this object is set to 'true', then the notifications are generated. If this object is set to 'false', then the notifications are not generated.

cpsmEfmdConfigTable.name: cpsmEfmdConfigTable
cpsmEfmdConfigTable.reference: Fabric Binding and Security Membership Data Distribution T11/02-187v2, December 3, 2002.
cpsmEfmdConfigTable.description: This table allows configuring EFMD on the local device. The configuration is on a per VSAN basis.

cpsmEfmdConfigEntry.name: cpsmEfmdConfigEntry
cpsmEfmdConfigEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmEfmdConfigEnforce.name: cpsmEfmdConfigEnforce
cpsmEfmdConfigEnforce.description: This object specifies whether the EFMD enforcement policy is strict or loose on this VSAN. If this object is set to 'true', then the enforcement policy is strict. As a result, if a device that tries to join the fabric thru' an E port on the local device does not pass the authorization check, it is not allowed access and the E port is isolated. If this object is set to 'false', then the enforcement policy is loose. As a result, if a device that tries to join the fabric thru' an E port on the local device does not pass the authorization check, it can still be allowed access.

cpsmPortBindNextFreeTable.name: cpsmPortBindNextFreeTable
cpsmPortBindNextFreeTable.description: This table contains the next free index value that can be used for creation of an entry in the cpsmPortBindTable. These values are maintained on a per VSAN/VLAN basis.

cpsmPortBindNextFreeEntry.name: cpsmPortBindNextFreeEntry
cpsmPortBindNextFreeEntry.description: An entry (concpetual row) in this table.

cpsmPortBindNextFreeNwIndex.name: cpsmPortBindNextFreeNwIndex
cpsmPortBindNextFreeNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmPortBindNextFreeNwType.

cpsmPortBindNextFreeIndex.name: cpsmPortBindNextFreeIndex
cpsmPortBindNextFreeIndex.description: Represents the next free index value for a port binding entry. If the value of this object is non-zero, then it represents the next free index value. If the value of this object is zero, then there are no more free indices available on this VSAN/VLAN.

cpsmFabricBindNextFreeTable.name: cpsmFabricBindNextFreeTable
cpsmFabricBindNextFreeTable.description: This table contains the next free index value that can be used for creation of an entry in the cpsmFabricBindTable. These values are maintained on a per VSAN/VLAN basis.

cpsmFabricBindNextFreeEntry.name: cpsmFabricBindNextFreeEntry
cpsmFabricBindNextFreeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table.

cpsmFabricBindNextFreeNwIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindNextFreeNwIndex
cpsmFabricBindNextFreeNwIndex.description: The id of the VSAN/VLAN according to the type specified in the corresponding instance of cpsmFabricBindNextFreeNwType.

cpsmFabricBindNextFreeIndex.name: cpsmFabricBindNextFreeIndex
cpsmFabricBindNextFreeIndex.description: Represents the next free index value for a fabric binding entry. If the value of this object is non-zero, then it represents the next free index value. If the value of this object is zero, then there are no more free indices available on this VSAN/VLAN.

ciscoPsmPortBindFPortDenyNotify.name: ciscoPsmPortBindFPortDenyNotify
ciscoPsmPortBindFPortDenyNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever a FLOGI is denied due to enforced port bindings on the local device on a F/FL port.

ciscoPsmPortBindEPortDenyNotify.name: ciscoPsmPortBindEPortDenyNotify
ciscoPsmPortBindEPortDenyNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever a switch is denied due to enforced port bindings on the local device on a E port.

ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotify.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotify
ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever a device is not allowed to join the fabric due to enforced fabric bindings on the local device.

ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotifyNew.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotifyNew
ciscoPsmFabricBindDenyNotifyNew.description: This notification is generated whenever a device is not allowed to join the fabric due to enforced fabric bindings on the local device.

ciscoPsmMIBCompliance.name: ciscoPsmMIBCompliance
ciscoPsmMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev1.name: ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev1
ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev1.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev4.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev5.name: ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev5
ciscoPsmMIBComplianceRev5.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Port Security Manager.

ciscoPsmPortBindConfigGroup.name: ciscoPsmPortBindConfigGroup
ciscoPsmPortBindConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying and configuring port bindings and activating them.

ciscoPsmFabricBindConfigGroup.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindConfigGroup
ciscoPsmFabricBindConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying and configuring fabric bindings and activating them.

ciscoPsmPortBindEnforcedGroup.name: ciscoPsmPortBindEnforcedGroup
ciscoPsmPortBindEnforcedGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying enforced port bindings.

ciscoPsmFabricBindEnforcedGroup.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindEnforcedGroup
ciscoPsmFabricBindEnforcedGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying enforced fabric bindings.

ciscoPsmPortBindStatsGroup.name: ciscoPsmPortBindStatsGroup
ciscoPsmPortBindStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying Port binding statistics and violation information.

ciscoPsmFabricBindStatsGroup.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindStatsGroup
ciscoPsmFabricBindStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying Fabric binding statistics and violation information.

ciscoPsmPortBindNotifyGroup.name: ciscoPsmPortBindNotifyGroup
ciscoPsmPortBindNotifyGroup.description: A collection of notification(s) for monitoring denial of FLOGI due to port bindings being enforced.

ciscoPsmFabricBindNotifyGroup.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindNotifyGroup
ciscoPsmFabricBindNotifyGroup.description: A collection of notification(s) for monitoring denial of request to join the fabric due to fabric bindings being enforced.

ciscoPsmPortBindAutoLearnGroup.name: ciscoPsmPortBindAutoLearnGroup
ciscoPsmPortBindAutoLearnGroup.description: A collection of object(s) for enabling/disabling auto learn of port bindings.

ciscoPsmFabricBindAutoLearnGroup.name: ciscoPsmFabricBindAutoLearnGroup
ciscoPsmFabricBindAutoLearnGroup.description: A collection of object(s) for enabling/disabling auto learn of fabric bindings.
